5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERoshan%20Gupta%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%2046-year-old%20business%20owner%20who%20moved%20to%20Portugal%20with%20his%20family%20in%202022.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20his%20former%20employment%20and%20identity.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20the%20traditional%20Silicon%20Valley%20story.%20I%20grew%20up%20loving%20technology%2C%20went%20to%20MIT%2C%20studied%20computer%20science%2C%20and%20got%20my%20first%20job%20at%20a%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20last%20role%20was%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-messages-android-update-iphone-reacted-texts-imessage-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20leading%20the%20Messages%20team%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20had%20a%20big%20team%20of%20product%20managers%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20300-plus%20org%20with%20a%20nine-digit%20budget.%20It%20was%20awesome.%20I%20loved%20the%20company%20and%20I%20loved%20the%20team%2C%20which%20is%20probably%20why%20people%20thought%20I%20was%20crazy%20for%20leaving%20and%20moving%20to%20Portugal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20make%20big%20changes%2C%20often%20there's%20this%20sort%20of%20big%20moment.%20But%20the%20truth%20is%2C%20it's%20a%20collection%20of%20all%20these%20other%20moments%20and%20the%20catalyst%20that%20finally%20puts%20you%20over%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%2C%20and%20eventually%20our%20two%20sons%2C%20like%20to%20be%20adventurous%2C%20but%20we%20were%20also%20on%20the%20path%20you're%20supposed%20to%20take%2C%20which%20is%20to%20get%20a%20job%2C%20earn%20a%20paycheck%2C%20work%20harder%2C%20and%20climb%20the%20corporate%20ladder.%20The%20adventures%20we%20had%20been%20taking%20would%20be%20like%20moving%20from%20California%20to%20Austin%20and%20then%20to%20Seattle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20COVID%2C%20we%20kept%20thinking%3A%20What%20if%20we%20made%20a%20bigger%20change%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22453d2798-56ec-4c31-8f02-3fd065b7bbcd%5C%22%3EThe%20catalyst%20was%20a%20tough%20work-life%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20enter%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-wall-street-investment-banking-after-fainting-bad-work-culture-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efield%20like%20investment%20banking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20know%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20grind%20%E2%80%94%20and%20often%2C%20you%20get%20in%20and%20you%20get%20out.%20I%20graduated%20back%20in%202000%20when%20the%20internet%20was%20booming.%20Mobile%20phones%20were%20just%20coming%20online.%20I%20was%20the%20first%20generation%20to%20be%20connected%2024%2F7%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20we've%20seen%20the%20effects%20of%20that%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20both%20worked%20in%20tech%20and%20we%20found%20that%20the%20more%20we%20did%20and%20the%20more%20success%20we%20had%20on%20paper%2C%20the%20worse%20our%20quality%20of%20life%20was%20getting.%20We%20were%20doing%20well%20from%20a%20career%20perspective%20and%20financially%20%E2%80%94%20but%20time%20for%20family%2C%20self-care%2C%20and%20community%20wasn't%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20option%20was%20to%20work%20like%20crazy%20for%2010%20more%20years%2C%20earn%20a%20crazy%20amount%20of%20money%2C%20and%20retire.%20But%20I%20didn't%20know%20if%20I%20could%20make%20it%2010%20years%20working%20at%20that%20pace.%20You%20don't%20know%20how%20much%20time%20you%20have%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20running%20the%20Messages%20team%2C%20I%20had%20teams%20in%20the%20US%20on%20different%20coasts%2C%20in%20Zurich%2C%20and%20in%20Asia.%20I%20would%20wake%20up%2C%20pick%20up%20my%20phone%2C%20and%20start%20working.%20I%20would%20get%20the%20kids%20out%20to%20school%2C%20and%20by%207%3A30%20or%208%3A00%20a.m.%2C%20I%20was%20in%20my%20seat%20taking%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20Google's%20Seattle%20office%2C%20but%20my%20teams%20were%20all%20over%20the%20world%2C%20so%20I%20would%20commute%20for%2045%20minutes%20to%20get%20on%20a%20video%20call.%20There%20are%20pros%20to%20being%20in%20the%20office%2C%20but%20there%20are%20also%20cons.%20So%20much%20of%20my%20work%20was%20on%20a%20video%20call%20talking%20to%20teams%20all%20over%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%206%20p.m.%20or%20so%2C%20I%20would%20force%20myself%20to%20get%20off%20because%20I%20had%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20kids.%20Then%20I%20would%20give%20them%20dinner%20and%20pop%20them%20in%20front%20of%20a%20TV%2C%20or%20try%20to%20spend%20some%20time%20with%20them%2C%20but%20I%20was%20already%20spent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20would%20get%20a%20flood%20of%20emails%20because%20Europe%20is%20waking%20up.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20got%20on%20top%20of%20that%20and%20was%20about%20to%20go%20to%20bed%20%E2%80%94%20surprise%2C%20Asia%20wakes%20up.%20When%20I%20wake%20up%20the%20next%20morning%2C%20I%20have%20all%20the%20stuff%20left%20over%20from%20there.%20Then%20the%20US%20is%20waking%20up%2C%20and%20you%20repeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20repeating%20that%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20previous%20job%20where%20I%20wasn't%20a%20product%20leader%2C%20I%20still%20felt%20overwhelmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20all%20try%20these%20tips%20and%20tricks%20like%20not%20checking%20emails%20after%20a%20certain%20time%20or%20scheduling%20emails%20to%20send%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20and%20then%20a%20month%20later%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftime-to-rethink-what-work-life-balance-really-means-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20would%20all%20go%20out%20the%20window%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we're%20all%20back%20to%20grinding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2257ade646-7196-4bd8-a32a-bebe5dd121a5%5C%22%3EI'm%20still%20busy%20in%20Portugal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20for%20moving%20was%20I%20wanted%20to%20try%20building%20my%20own%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20Type%20I%20Diabetes%20and%20I%20felt%20I%20could%20never%20be%20an%20entrepreneur%20in%20the%20US%20because%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20afford%20healthcare%20for%20myself%20and%20my%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Portugal%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20start%20a%20company%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FAmplifyPM.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmplifyPM%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20help%20senior%20product%20managers%20become%20product%20leaders%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20teach%20them%20how%20to%20scale%20and%20handle%20the%20increase%20of%20responsibility%20in%20a%20sustainable%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20if%20I%20came%20to%20Portugal%20and%20took%20a%20break%20from%20work%20and%20started%20my%20own%20business%2C%20I%20would%20suddenly%20have%20oodles%20of%20free%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20feel%20busy.%20The%20difference%20is%20the%20pace%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20with%20companies%20like%20Google%20and%20others%20felt%20like%20drinking%20out%20of%20a%20fire%20hose.%20You%20sit%20down%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20work%20you%20get%20done%20in%20that%20same%20amount%20of%20time%20is%20off%20the%20charts%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20get%20promoted%2C%20you%20likely%20get%20promoted%20because%20you%20have%20the%20capacity%20to%20handle%20more.%20At%20Google%2C%20I%20loved%20the%20team%2C%20the%20company%2C%20and%20what%20we%20did.%20That%20let%20me%20handle%20such%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20things%20because%20I%20found%20meaning%20in%20my%20work%2C%20but%20it%20was%20not%20enough%20for%20us%20as%20a%20family%20to%20keep%20going%20in%20that%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Portugal%2C%20I'm%20spending%20that%20time%20at%20a%20more%20sustainable%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20want%20the%20lesson%20to%20be%20that%20if%20you%20have%20a%20career%20in%20Big%20Tech%2C%20the%20only%20way%20to%20thrive%20is%20to%20leave.%20This%20career%20unlocked%20so%20much%20for%20us%20and%20I%20don't%20regret%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20culture%20that%20keeps%20pushing%20you%2C%20but%20