ved.%20Russia%20is%20developing%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussias-new-icbm-keeps-failing-leaving-older-and-inferior-missiles-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheavy%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hypersonic%20missiles%2C%20and%20nuclear-powered%20cruise%20missiles.%20China%20has%20also%20developed%20new%20hypersonic%20weapons%2C%20and%20even%20North%20Korea%20is%20building%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorth-korea-new-icbm-missile-test-how-effective-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emodern%20ICBMs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20advanced%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225244%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vehicles%20carrying%20DF-17%20missiles%20participate%20in%20a%20military%20parade.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb968acfb7f307e572f9ab%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223496%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVehicles%20carrying%20DF-17%20missiles%20participate%20in%20a%20military%20parade.%3Cp%3EGREG%20BAKER%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIntercepting%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-and-japan-teaming-up-to-defeat-hypersonic-missiles-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehypersonic%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20traditional%20missile%20defense%20systems%20is%20difficult%20due%20to%20their%20high%20speeds%2C%20irregular%20flight%20paths%2C%20and%20maneuverability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20the%20more%20traditional%20threats%20pose%20significant%20challenges%20that%20can%20exceed%20US%20defensive%20capabilities.%20Modern%20missiles%20are%20often%20equipped%20with%20countermeasures%20to%20defeat%20interceptors%2C%20and%20the%20sheer%20size%20of%20certain%20adversary%20arsenals%20exceeds%20what%20current%20American%20defenses%20can%20handle.%20Russia%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20roughly%201%2C700%20deployed%20nuclear%20weapons.%20Any%20one%20could%20destroy%20an%20American%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202023%20report%20from%20a%20congressional%20commission%20on%20US%20strategic%20posture%20said%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20%26quot%3Bshould%20focus%20on%20sensor%20architectures%2C%20integrated%20command%20and%20control%2C%20interceptors%2C%20cruise%20and%20hypersonic%20missile%20defenses%2C%20and%20area%20or%20point%20defenses.%26quot%3B%20It%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20DOD%20should%20urgently%20pursue%20deployment%20of%20any%20capabilities%20that%20prove%20feasible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20long%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-force-orders-new-missile-warning-satellites-to-bolster-defense-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadditional%20space-based%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20needed%20to%20defeat%20evolving%20missile%20threats.%20Trump's%20plan%20emphasizes%20both%20space%20sensors%20and%20space%20interceptors%20for%20detecting%20launches%20immediately%20and%20attacking%20missiles%20outside%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETom%20Karako%2C%20a%20missile%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20space-based%20interceptors%20are%20essential%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20of%20where%20things%20are%20going%20in%20terms%20of%20space%20becoming%20a%20warfighting%20domain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20this%20year%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20see%20a%20different%20national%20conversation%20about%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20executive%20order%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20create%20big%20opportunities%20for%20leading%20air%20defense%20manufacturers%20like%20Lockheed%20Martin%2C%20Northrop%20Grumman%2C%20and%20RTX.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20the%20new%20Iron%20Dome%20for%20America%20on%20a%20recent%20earnings%20call%2C%20Lockheed's%20CFO%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20can%20shoot%20down%20cruise%20missiles%20with%20lasers%20now%2C%20and%20that%20could%20be%20part%20of%20the%20solution.%26quot%3B%20And%20RTX's%20chief%20financial%20officer%20recently%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bnnbloomberg.ca%2Fbusiness%2Fcompany-news%2F2025%2F01%2F28%2Frtx-beats-quarterly-profit-estimates-offers-muted-2025-outlook%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20fully%20prepared%20to%20support%20the%20president's%20ambitions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20gives%20Secretary%20of%20Defense%20Pete%20Hegseth%2060%20days%20to%20deliver%20a%20plan%20for%20constructing%20a%20next-generation%20shield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225be16f39-26e8-4ab4-bbbe-49a84af9154a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20'Star%20Wars'%20to%20'Iron%20Dome%20for%20America'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20had%20a%20vision%20for%20a%20missile%20shield%20that%20would%20change%20the%20deterrence%20model.%20It%20would%20feature%20ground-based%20capabilities%2C%20sensor%20systems%2C%20directed-energy%20weapons%20like%20lasers%2C%20space-based%20interceptors%2C%20and%20more%20to%20revolutionize%20defense%20in%20the%20nuclear%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20if%20free%20people%20could%20live%20secure%20in%20the%20knowledge%20that%20their%20security%20did%20not%20rest%20upon%20the%20threat%20of%20instant%20US%20retaliation%20to%20deter%20a%20Soviet%20attack%2C%20that%20we%20could%20intercept%20and%20destroy%20strategic%20ballistic%20missiles%20before%20they%20reached%20our%20own%20soil%20or%20that%20of%20our%20allies%3F%26quot%3B%20Reagan%20said%20in%201983%20as%20he%20announced%20the%20SDI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReagan%20called%20on%20the%20scientific%20community%20that%20created%20nuclear%20weapons%20to%20develop%20the%20capability%20to%20make%20them%20obsolete%20and%20end%20the%20principle%20of%20mutually%20assured%20destruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20of%20the%20ambitious%20defense%20program%20derisively%20called%20it%20%26quot%3BStar%20Wars%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20risked%20destabilizing%20the%20traditional%20deterrence%20approach%20and%20igniting%20a%20new%20arms%20race.%20The%20program%20was%20scrapped%20in%20the%20early%201990s%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20but%20elements%20of%20it%20live%20on%20in%20today's%20Missile%20Defense%20Agency%2C%20which%20oversees%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-wants-us-shield-like-iron-dome-long-shot-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eground-based%20midcourse%20defense%3C%2Fa%3E%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GMD%20system%2C%20part%20of%20a%20layered%20defense%2C%20has%20a%20less%20than%20astounding%20intercept%20success%20rate.%20The%20MDA%2C%20in%20partnership%20with%20firms%20like%20Boeing%2C%20Northrup%20Grumman%2C%20and%20Lockheed%2C%20has%20worked%20to%20improve%20it%20through%20new%20systems%20and%20next-generation%20interceptors%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20it%20remains%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GMD%20system%20is%20aimed%20at%20combating%20lower-level%20threats%2C%20like%20those%20posed%20by%20North%20Korea's%20relatively%20young%20ICBM%20program.%20For%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20the%20US%20relies%20on%20the%20threat%20of%20instant%20nuclear%20retaliation%20as%20a%20deterrent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20interceptor%20missiles%20takes%20flight%20from%20a%20coastal%20area.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679aa78a196626c40985bc18%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20interceptor%20missile%20takes%20flight%20in%20pursuit%20of%20an%20ICBM%20during%20a%20test%20of%20the%20Ground-based%20Midcourse%20Defense%20(GMD)%20system.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20signaled%20dissatisfaction%20with%20current%20capabilities%20and%20invoked%20Reagan%20when%20signing%20the%20order%20for%20a%20next-generation%20shield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Ronald%20Reagan%20endeavored%20to%20build%20an%20effective%20defense%20against%20nuclear%20attacks%2C%20and%20while%20this%20program%20resulted%20in%20many%20technological%20advances%2C%20it%20was%20canceled%20before%20its%20goal%20could%20be%20realized%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20proposal%20calls%20for%20the%20development%20and%20deployment%20of%20space-based%20sensors%20and%20interceptors%2C%20options%20to%20defeat%20missile%20salvos%20before%20launch%20and%20disrupt%20missiles%20without%20destroying%20them%2C%20and%20underlayer%20and%20terminal%20defense%20systems.%20The%20details%20are%20few%20for%20now%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20appears%20to%20rely%20heavily%20on%20space%2C%20left-of-launch%2C%20and%20directed-energy%20capabilities.%20The%20US%20is%20much%20further%20on%20these%20technologies%20today%20than%20it%20was%20in%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20space-based%20interceptor%20is%20essentially%20an%20orbital%20missile%20launcher%20with%20the%20speed%20and%20range%20to%20strike%20an%20ICBM%20outside%20the%20atmosphere.%20Reagan's%20version%20was%20called%20the%20Brilliant%20Pebbles%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20to%20boost%20defenses%20comes%20amid%20increased%20focus%20on%20the%20threats%20posed%20by%20near-peer%20challengers.%20China%20has%20rapidly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-600-nukes-pentagon-advanced-systems-hgv-fob-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpanded%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOstensibly%2C%20the%20%5Bexecutive%20order%5D%20is%20saying%20we%20need%20to%20be%20more%20attentive%20to%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Karako%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20I%20would%20think%20that's%20the%20right%20answer.%26quot%3B%20As%20for%20whether%20this%20plan%20will%20sufficiently%20address%20the%20challenges%20the%20US%20faces%2C%20he%20said%20we'll%20have%20to%20wait%20and%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b187eeee-1816-4acc-a27c-289ffab34674%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EReignited%20classic%20debates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BIron%20Dome%20for%20America%26quot%3B%20program%20is%20to%20shield%20the%20US%20from%20attack%20while%20preserving%20its%20second-strike%20capability%2C%20where%20the%20US%20preserves%20enough%20nuclear%20force%20after%20an%20attack%20to%20deter%20an%20enemy%20from%20striking%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%20the%20shield%20and%20traditional%20deterrence%20would%20theoretically%20work%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHans%20Kristensen%2C%20a%20nuclear%20weapons%20expert%20with%20the%20Federation%20of%20American%20Scientists%2C%20called%20Trump's%20plan%20%26quot%3BSDI%20v2%2C%26quot%3B%20characterizing%20the%20vision%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20mix%20of%20existing%20capabilities%2C%20emerging%20ones%2C%20and%20pipe%20dreams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnkit%20Panda%2C%20a%20nuclear%20policy%20expert%20at%20the%20Carnegie%20Endowment%20for%20International%20Peace%2C%20said%20that%20the%20goal%20of%20making%20the%20continental%20US%20invulnerable%20to%20missile%20attacks%20%26quot%3Bremains%20a%20mirage%20and%20a%20path%20to%20endless%20spending%20and%20arms%20racing.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bcheaper%20launch%20costs%20and%20new%20interceptor%20tech%20won't%20change%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225307%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20A-10%20flies%20over%20a%20US%20boomer%20submarine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679aa7397bb3f854015b1895%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223538%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20A-10%20ground-attack%20aircraft%20flies%20over%20the%20Ohio-class%20ballistic%20missile%20submarine%20USS%20Nebraska.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%202nd%20Class%20Gwendelyn%20Ohrazda%2FReleased%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20the%20US%20relies%20on%20diplomacy%20and%20deterrence%20to%20ensure%20security%2C%20he%20said.%20Arms%20control%20is%20a%20much%20cheaper%20route%20to%20safety%2C%20with%20rigorous%20verification%20processes%20in%20place.%20Trump%20recently%20said%20that%20he%20would%20like%20to%20see%20the%20mutual%20reduction%20and%20even%20elimination%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20through%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENuclear%20missile%20defense%20is%20exceptionally%20difficult%20and%20will%20likely%20remain%20so%2C%20even%20with%20a%20working%20missile%20shield.%20CSIS's%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EKarako%20said%20that%20if%20Russia%20woke%20up%20and%20chose%20to%20lob%201%2C000%20warheads%20at%20the%20US%2C%20the%20shield%20would%20be%20insufficient.%20But%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20stronger%20defenses%20raise%20the%20threshold%20for%20an%20attack%2C%20boosting%20deterrence%20against%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20limited%20or%20coercive%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20experts%2C%20such%20as%20Hudson%20Institute's%20Rebeccah%20Heinrichs%20and%20retired%20Gen.%20John%20Hyten%2C%20former%20vice%20chairman%20of%20the%20Joint%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%2C%20have%20made%20similar%20points%2C%20suggesting%20that%20the%20US%20should%20%26quot%3Bdeploy%20additional%20missile%20defense%20capabilities%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bdeter%20both%20Russia%20and%20China%20from%20considering%20such%20an%20attack%2C%20by%20increasing%20their%20uncertainty%20over%20whether%20it%20would%20succeed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20arms%20control%20community%20holds%20the%20view%20that%20better%20shields%20only%20drive%20adversaries%20to%20build%20better%20spears.%20To%20that%20point%2C%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20repeatedly%20highlighted%20the%20ability%20of%20his%20newest%20weapons%20to%20evade%20existing%20missile-defense%20systems%2C%20suggesting%20that%20may%20have%20been%20a%20motivation.%20Others%2C%20however%2C%20argue%20that%20US%20rivals%20and%20foes%20will%20build%20the%20tools%20to%20challenge%20US%20power%20regardless%20of%20what%20defenses%20America%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-iron-dome-for-america-plan-for-next-generation-shield-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738488361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679aa798eb4be2fff9a2db57%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-iron-dome-for-america-plan-for-next-generation-shield-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump's%20push%20follows%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20Reagan's%20Strategic%20Defense%20Initiative%2C%20a%20scrapped%20program%20popularly%20called%20%26quot%3BStar%20Wars.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rpickrell%40businessinsider.com%20(Ryan%20Pickrell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-iron-dome-for-america-plan-for-next-generation-shield-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Jhaadu%20ke%20tinke%20bikhar%20rahe%20hain%2C'%20says%20PM%20Modi%20on%20AAP%20leaders%20quitting%20party%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738488309000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117855818%2Cimgsize-639759.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fdelhi-polls-jhaadu-ke-tinke-bikhar-rahe-hain-says-pm-modi-on-aap-leaders-quitting-party%2Farticleshow%2F117855728.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20criticised%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20ahead%20of%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20elections%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20falling%20apart%20due%20to%20internal%20defections.%20He%20expressed%20confidence%20in%20BJP%20forming%20the%20next%20government%2C%20following%20several%20AAP%20leaders%20joining%20the%20BJP.%20Modi%20also%20praised%20the%20recently%20announced%20Union%20Budget%2C%20highlighting%20tax%20relief%20for%20the%20middle%20class.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NDTV%20Explainer%3A%202%20Generals%20At%20Centre%20Of%20World's%20Worst%20Humanitarian%20Crisis%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDrone%20strikes%2C%20severely%20hit%20infrastructure%2C%20widespread%20starvation%2C%20social%20media%20ban%2C%20thousands%20dead%20and%20millions%20displaced%20-%20the%20toll%20of%20the%20civil%20war%20in%20Sudan%20continues%20to%20mount%20with%20each%20passing%20day%2C%20pegging%20it%20as%20a%20dire%20humanitarian%20crisis.%20The%20latest%20among%20a%20series%20of%20attacks%20was%20artillery%20shelling%20and%20air%20strikes%20in%20capital%20Khartoum%20on%20Saturday%20that%20killed%20at%20least%2056%20people.%20Over%20two%20years%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20the%20United%20States%20accused%20a%20militia%20commander%20of%20%26quot%3Bcommitting%20genocide%26quot%3B%20against%20non-Arab%20minority%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGenesis%20Of%20Conflict%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESudan%20has%20witnessed%20violence%20and%20displacement%20since%20the%202003%20Darfur%20ethnic%20cleansing%20crisis%2C%20and%20has%20the%20second-highest%20refugee%20population%20in%20Africa.%20After%20Authoritarian%20leader%20Omar%20al-Bashir%20was%20deposed%20as%20President%20in%202019%2C%20Sudan%20began%20a%20journey%20of%20reforms%20as%20it%20transitioned%20to%20a%20new%20government.%20This%20included%20reforms%20in%20the%20Sudanese%20Armed%20Forces%20(SAF)%20and%20the%20paramilitary%20Rapid%20Support%20Forces%20(RSF)%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RSF%20is%20an%20independent%20paramilitary%20force%2C%20and%20used%20to%20fight%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Sudanese%20government.%20The%20RSF%20was%20founded%20by%20over%2020%20years%20ago%20to%20quash%20rebellions%20in%20Darfur%2C%20where%20they%20carried%20out%20a%20campaign%20of%20ethnic%20violence%20against%20Masalit%20communities.%20Reforms%20that%20would%20impact%20the%20RSF%20and%20SAF%20sparked%20tensions%20between%20the%20two%20factions.%20This%20also%20resulted%20in%20tension%20between%20Bashir%20and%20General%20Abdel%20Fattah%20al-Burhan%2C%20who%20has%20been%20Sudan's%20de%20facto%20leader%20since%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBashir's%20removal%20in%202019%20had%20sparked%20hope%20for%20civilian%20rule%20in%20Sudan.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20al-Burhan%20and%20Lt.%20Gen.%20Mohamed%20Hamdan%2C%20who%20leads%20the%20RSF%20and%20is%20also%20known%20as%20Hemedti%2C%20united%20to%20seize%20power%20in%20a%20military%20coup%2C%20but%20the%20two%20soon%20fell%20out.%20Diplomats%2C%20including%20those%20from%20United%20States%2C%20attempted%20to%20broker%20peace%2C%20but%20confusion%20prevailed%20over%20RSF's%20absorption%20into%20the%20army.%20This%20plunged%20the%20country%20into%20political%20and%20economic%20turmoil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%20in%20Sudan%20began%20when%20violent%20clashes%20erupted%20between%20SAF%20and%20RSF%20erupted%20in%20the%20capital%20Khartoum%20in%20April%202023.%20The%20unrest%20soon%20spread%20to%20areas%20like%20Darfur%2C%20North%20Kordofan%20and%20Gezira%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMillions%20Displaced%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20April%2015%2C%202023%2C%20and%20October%2025%2C%202024%2C%20the%20warring%20sides%20exchanged%20a%20total%20of%208%2C942%20attacks%2C%20averaging%2016%20a%20day%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Armed%20Conflict%20Location%20and%20Event%20Data%20Project%20(ACLED)%2C%20a%20crisis%20mapping%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%20resulted%20in%20over%2011%20million%20people%20being%20displaced%2C%20including%20internally%20displaced%20people%20(IDPs)%2C%20asylum%20seekers%20and%20refugees.%20A%20large%20chunk%20of%20Sudan's%20population%20now%20faces%20extreme%20shortages%20of%20food%2C%20water%2C%20medicine%20and%20fuel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENearly%20three%20quarters%20of%20health%20facilities%20are%20out%20of%20service%20and%20diseases%20including%20cholera%2C%20measles%20and%20malaria%20are%20spreading%20at%20a%20time%20when%20two%20thirds%20of%20the%20population%20lack%20access%20to%20health%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEgypt%20is%20hosting%20the%20most%20Sudanese%20refugees%20(1.2%20million)%2C%20followed%20by%20Chad%20(712%2C288)%2C%20South%20Sudan%20(190%2C280)%2C%20Libya%20(180%2C000)%2C%20Uganda%20(60%2C808)%20and%20Ethiopia%20(39%2C984).%20In%20South%20Sudan%2C%20most%20of%20those%20arriving%20are%20returning%20nationals%20(650%2C000)%20who%20had%20been%20living%20in%20Sudan%20as%20refugees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImpact%20On%20Women%20And%20Children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20estimates%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20over%203%20million%20women%20and%20girls%20were%20at%20risk%20of%20gender-based%20violence.%20The%20civil%20war%20only%20compounded%20it.%20Reports%20of%20rape%2C%20sexual%20slavery%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20sexual%20violence%20emerged%20only%20days%20after%20the%20conflict%20began.%20Attacks%20on%20healthcare%20facilities%2C%20equipment%20and%20workers%20are%20further%20depriving%20women%20and%20girls%20of%20lifesaving%20care%2C%20with%20pregnant%20women%20hardest%20hit%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20and%20UNFPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20UNICEF%2C%20Sudan%20is%20witnessing%20the%20world's%20largest%20child%20displacement%20crisis.%20The%20conflict%20has%20deprived%20millions%20of%20Sudanese%20children%20of%20an%20education%2C%20with%20more%20than%2090%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20country's%2019%20million%20school-age%20children%20having%20no%20access%20to%20formal%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Is%20The%20Current%20Situation%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20in%20a%20series%20of%20incidents%20of%20bloodshed%20was%20artillery%20shelling%20and%20air%20strikes%20killed%20at%20least%2056%20people%20and%20injured%20over%20150%20others%20across%20greater%20Khartoum%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShelling%20was%20reported%20at%20a%20camp%20for%20displaced%20people%20in%20El-Fasher%20in%20North%20Darfur%20that%20killed%20nine%20civilians%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20while%20on%20January%2024%2C%20a%20drone%20attack%20on%20a%20maternity%20hospital%20in%20El-Fasher%2C%20attributed%20to%20the%20RSF%2C%20left%20at%20least%2067%20dead%20and%2019%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20rights%20chief%20said%20that%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20alarmed%26quot%3B%20by%20reports%20of%20summary%20executions%20of%20civilians%20in%20Khartoum%20North%2C%20allegedly%20by%20Sudanese%20army%20fighters%20and%20allied%20militia.%20%26quot%3BDeliberately%20taking%20the%20life%20of%20a%20civilian%20or%20anyone%20not%20or%20no%20longer%20directly%20taking%20part%20in%20hostilities%20is%20a%20war%20crime%2C%26quot%3B%20Volker%20Turk%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20The%20statement%20noted%20a%20video%20circulated%20Thursday%20showing%20men%20in%20SAF%20uniform%20and%20members%20of%20the%20Al%20Baraa%20Bin%20Malik%20Brigade%20in%20Khartoum%20North%20%26quot%3Breading%20out%20a%20long%20list%20of%20names%20of%20alleged%20RSF%20collaborators%2C%20saying%20'Zaili'%20--%20Arabic%20for%20'killed'%20--%20after%20each%20name%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Rapid%20Support%20Forces%20dominate%20much%20of%20Khartoum%20and%20Darfur%2C%20while%20Wad%20Madani%20was%20captured%20in%20December.%20Later%2C%20however%2C%20the%20SAF%20recaptured%20Omdurman.%20The%20military%20also%20controls%20most%20of%20northern%20and%20eastern%20Sudan%2C%20including%20Port%20Sudan%20on%20the%20Red%20Sea.%20The%20paramilitary%20group%20also%20surrounded%20El%20Fasher%2C%20the%20last%20city%20in%20Darfur%20still%20held%20by%20the%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20army-allied%20militia%20claimed%20control%20of%20the%20towns%20of%20Tamboul%2C%20Rufaa%2C%20Al-Hasaheisa%20and%20Al-Hilaliya%2C%20some%20125%20kilometres%20(77%20miles)%20southeast%20of%20the%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESudan's%20military%20has%20used%20chemical%20weapons%20on%20at%20least%20two%20occasions%20against%20the%20paramilitary%20group%20it%20is%20battling%20for%20control%20of%20the%20country%2C%20four%20senior%20United%20States%20officials%20were%20reported%20as%20saying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F01%2F16%2Fworld%2Fafrica%2Fsudan-chemical-weapons-sanctions.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BUnder%20Burhan's%20leadership%2C%20the%20SAF's%20war%20tactics%20have%20included%20indiscriminate%20bombing%20of%20civilian%20infrastructure%2C%20attacks%20on%20schools%2C%20markets%2C%20and%20hospitals%2C%20and%20extrajudicial%20executions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Treasury%20Department%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAid%20Delivery%20Restricted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20catastrophic%20threats%20of%20famine%2C%20both%20the%20SAF%20and%20RSF%20are%20actively%20restricting%20aid%20delivery%20across%20Sudan.%20International%20organisations%20like%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme%20said%20that%20they%20cannot%20access%2090%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20people%20facing%20emergency%20levels%20of%20hunger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20high-level%20donor%20conference%20in%20Paris%20in%20April%2C%20international%20donors%20pledged%20more%20than%20two%20billion%20euros%20(or%20over%20%242.1%20billion)%20in%20aid%20for%20Sudan.%20But%20by%20June%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%20said%2C%20it%20had%20raised%20only%20%24430%20million%20of%20the%20%242.7%20billion%20it%20needs%20for%20Sudan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20Disasters%20Exacerbate%20Suffering%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20civil%20war%20continues%20amid%20sever%20droughts%20to%20floods%20to%20even%20a%20famine%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%20The%20conflict%20also%20exacerbated%20many%20of%20Sudan's%20existing%20challenges%2C%20including%20ongoing%20conflicts%2C%20disease%20outbreaks%2C%20and%20economic%20and%20political%20instability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Is%20The%20World%20Invested%20In%20The%20Conflict%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third-largest%20African%20country%20Sudan%20is%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20gold%20producers%20of%20the%20continent%20and%20its%20position%20on%20River%20Nile%20gives%20it%20agricultural%20potential.%20It%20is%20also%20situated%20on%20the%20coast%20of%20the%20Red%20Sea%2C%20a%20busy%20shipping%20route%2C%20for%20about%20500%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20sanctioned%20both%20Hemeti%20and%20Burhan%2C%20accusing%20the%20former%20of%20genocide%20and%20the%20latter%20of%20attacking%20schools%2C%20markets%20and%20hospitals%2C%20as%20well%20as%20using%20food%20deprivation%20as%20a%20weapon%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnited%20Arab%20Emirates%20was%20accused%20by%20the%20US%20of%20arming%20the%20RSF.%20Later%2C%20two%20Democrats%20agreed%20to%20lift%20objections%20to%20a%20%241.2%20billion%20arms%20sale%20to%20the%20UAE%20by%20the%20then%20administration%20of%20fellow%20Democrat%20Joe%20Biden%20after%20the%20White%20House%20said%20the%20Gulf%20power%20assured%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20now%20transferring%20any%20weapons%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20paramilitary%20group.%20The%20UAE%20has%20repeatedly%20denied%20arming%20the%20RSF%20despite%20international%20criticism%20and%20a%20finding%20by%20United%20Nations%20experts%20that%20the%20allegations%20were%20credible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20Wagner%20mercenaries%20also%20backed%20the%20RSF%20with%20weapons%20in%20the%20early%20months%20of%20the%20war%2C%20UN%20and%20Sudanese%20officials%20said%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Farticle%2Fsudan-khartoum-military.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20country%20is%20also%20receiving%20armed%20drones%20from%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738488240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fl04cb6so_sudan-explainer_625x300_02_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fndtv-explainer-how-the-worlds-worst-humanitarian-crisis-unfolded-in-sudan-7615535%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Drone%20strikes%2C%20severely%20hit%20infrastructure%2C%20widespread%20starvation%2C%20thousands%20dead%20and%20millions%20displaced%20-%20the%20toll%20of%20the%20civil%20war%20in%20Sudan%20continues%20to%20mount%20with%20each%20passing%20day.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fndtv-explainer-how-the-worlds-worst-humanitarian-crisis-unfolded-in-sudan-7615535%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cheap%20AI%20could%20be%20good%20for%20workers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221431%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tricia%20Goh%20looking%20at%20her%20desktop%20computer%20while%20coding.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67483732fa0140cdd56612e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20costs%20fall%20for%20artificial%20intelligence%20tools%2C%20more%20workers%20could%20gain%20access%20to%20the%20technology.%3Cp%3ETricia%20Goh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELower-cost%20AI%20tools%20could%20reshape%20jobs%20by%20giving%20more%20workers%20access%20to%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECompanies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepseek-r1-open-source-replicate-ai-west-china-hugging-face-2025-1%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeepSeek%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20developing%20low-cost%20AI%20that%20could%20help%20some%20workers%20get%20more%20done.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere%20could%20still%20be%20risks%20to%20workers%20if%20employers%20turn%20to%20bots%20for%20easy-to-automate%20tasks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexplaining-deepseek-chinese-models-efficiency-scaring-markets-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECut-rate%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20be%20shaking%20up%20industry%20giants%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20likely%20to%20take%20your%20job%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20not%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELower-cost%20approaches%20to%20developing%20and%20training%20artificial%20intelligence%20tools%2C%20from%20upstarts%20like%20China's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepseek-fuels-nvidia-h200-demand-cloud-cheaper-workload-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeepSeek%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20heavyweights%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-launches-o3-mini-ai-model-amid-deepseek-concerns-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20will%20likely%20allow%20more%20people%20to%20latch%20onto%20AI's%20productivity%20superpowers%2C%20industry%20observers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20workers%20worried%20that%20robots%20will%20take%20their%20jobs%2C%20that's%20a%20welcome%20development.%20One%20scary%20prospect%20has%20been%20that%20discount%20AI%20would%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20employers%20to%20swap%20in%20cheap%20bots%20for%20pricey%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20that%20could%20still%20happen.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20technology%20will%20likely%20muscle%20aside%20some%20entry-level%20workers%20or%20those%20whose%20roles%20largely%20consist%20of%20repetitive%20tasks%20that%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fto-find-or-keep-a-job-become-a-specialist-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeasy%20to%20automate%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20higher%20up%20the%20food%20chain%2C%20staff%20aren't%20necessarily%20free%20from%20AI's%20reach.%20Salesforce%20CEO%20Marc%20Benioff%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.itpro.com%2Fsoftware%2Fdevelopment%2Fmaybe-we-arent-going-to-hire-anybody-this-year-marc-benioff-says-salesforce-might-not-hire-any-software-engineers-in-2025-as-the-firm-reaps-the-benefits-of-ai-agents%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDevelopment-%2C%2527Maybe%2520we%2520aren%2527t%2520going%2520to%2520hire%2520anybody%2520this%2520year%2Cthe%2520benefits%2520of%2520AI%2520agents%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20this%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company%20might%20not%20hire%20any%20software%20engineers%20in%202025%20because%20the%20firm%20is%20having%20so%20much%20luck%20with%20AI%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20broadly%2C%20for%20many%20workers%2C%20lower-cost%20AI%20is%20likely%20to%20expand%20who%20can%20access%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20becomes%20cheaper%2C%20it's%20easier%20to%20integrate%20AI%20so%20that%20it%20becomes%20%26quot%3Ba%20sidekick%20instead%20of%20a%20threat%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarah%20Wittman%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20George%20Mason%20University's%20Costello%20College%20of%20Business%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20AI's%20price%20falls%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20more%20of%20a%20widespread%20acceptance%20of%2C%20'Oh%2C%20this%20is%20the%20way%20we%20can%20work.'%26quot%3B%20That's%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20mindset%20of%20AI%20being%20a%20pricey%20add-on%20that%20employers%20might%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20justifying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e18b7f4b-a5b0-4f5c-b927-c7f2bda15344%5C%22%3EAI%20for%20all%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECheaper%20AI%20could%20benefit%20workers%20in%20areas%20of%20a%20business%20that%20often%20aren't%20seen%20as%20direct%20revenue%20generators%2C%20Arturo%20Devesa%2C%20chief%20AI%20architect%20at%20the%20analytics%20and%20data%20company%20EXL%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20were%20not%20going%20to%20get%20a%20copilot%2C%20maybe%20in%20marketing%20and%20HR%2C%20and%20now%20you%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevesa%20said%20the%20path%20shown%20by%20companies%20like%20DeepSeek%20in%20slashing%20the%20cost%20of%20developing%20and%20implementing%20large%20language%20models%20changes%20the%20calculus%20for%20employers%20deciding%20where%20AI%20might%20pay%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%2C%20for%20most%20large%20companies%2C%20such%20determinations%20factor%20in%20cost%2C%20accuracy%2C%20and%20speed.%20Now%2C%20with%20some%20expenses%20falling%2C%20the%20possibilities%20of%20where%20AI%20could%20show%20up%20in%20a%20workplace%20will%20mushroom%2C%20Devesa%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20echoes%20the%20axiom%20that's%20suddenly%20everywhere%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20AI%20gets%20more%20efficient%20and%20accessible%2C%20we%20will%20see%20its%20use%20skyrocket%2C%20turning%20it%20into%20a%20commodity%20we%20just%20can't%20get%20enough%20of%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-reacts-deepseek-chinese-ai-upending-tech-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote%20on%20X%20on%20Monday%20about%20the%20so-called%20Jevons%20paradox.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevesa%20said%20that%20more%20productive%20workers%20won't%20necessarily%20reduce%20demand%20for%20people%20if%20employers%20can%20develop%20new%20markets%20and%20new%20sources%20of%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f511172-c674-4fe5-872b-1a00a02ea74c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20as%20a%20commodity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Bates%2C%20CEO%20of%20software%20company%20SER%20Group%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20AI%20is%20becoming%20a%20commodity%20much%20quicker%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20that%20for%20tasks%20where%20desk%20workers%20might%20need%20a%20backup%20or%20someone%20to%20double-check%20their%20work%2C%20low-cost%20AI%20might%20be%20able%20to%20step%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20great%20as%20the%20junior%20knowledge%20worker%2C%20the%20thing%20that%20scales%20a%20human%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBates%2C%20a%20former%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20Cambridge%20University%2C%20said%20that%20even%20if%20an%20employer%20already%20planned%20to%20use%20AI%2C%20the%20reduced%20costs%20would%20boost%20return%20on%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20lower-priced%20AI%20could%20give%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20businesses%20easier%20access%20to%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20going%20to%20open%20things%20up%20to%20more%20folks%2C%26quot%3B%20Bates%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bbb41054-e47d-4fb4-aacc-95bfea255eae%5C%22%3EEmployers%20still%20need%20humans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20lower-cost%20AI%2C%20humans%20will%20still%20have%20a%20place%2C%20said%20Yakov%20Filippenko%2C%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Intch%2C%20which%20helps%20professionals%20find%20part-time%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20as%20tech%20firms%20compete%20on%20price%20and%20drive%20down%20the%20cost%20of%20AI%2C%20many%20employers%20still%20won't%20be%20eager%20to%20remove%20workers%20from%20every%20loop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Filippenko%20said%20companies%20will%20continue%20to%20need%20developers%20because%20someone%20has%20to%20verify%20that%20new%20code%20does%20what%20an%20employer%20wants.%20He%20said%20companies%20hire%20recruiters%20not%20just%20to%20complete%20manual%20work%3B%20bosses%20also%20want%20a%20recruiter's%20opinion%20on%20a%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20pay%20for%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20Filippenko%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Conover%2C%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Brightwave%2C%20a%20research%20platform%20that%20uses%20AI%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20a%20good%20chunk%20of%20what%20people%20do%20in%20desk%20jobs%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20consists%20of%20tasks%20that%20could%20be%20automated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20AI%20that's%20more%20widely%20available%20because%20of%20falling%20costs%20will%20allow%20humans'%20creative%20abilities%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bfreed%20up%20by%20orders%20of%20magnitude%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20sophistication%20of%20the%20problems%20we%20can%20solve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConover%20thinks%20that%20as%20prices%20fall%2C%20AI%20intelligence%20will%20also%20spread%20to%20far%20more%20areas.%20He%20said%20it's%20akin%20to%20how%2C%20decades%20ago%2C%20the%20only%20motor%20in%20a%20car%20might%20have%20been%20under%20the%20hood.%20Later%2C%20as%20electric%20motors%20shrank%2C%20they%20showed%20up%20in%20places%20like%20rear-view%20mirrors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20now%20it's%20in%20your%20toothbrush%2C%26quot%3B%20Conover%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Conover%20said%20omnipresent%20AI%20will%20let%20professionals%20create%20systems%20that%20they%20can%20tailor%20to%20the%20needs%20of%20jobs%20and%20workflows.%20That%20will%20let%20AI%20bots%20handle%20much%20of%20the%20grunt%20work%20and%20allow%20workers%20willing%20to%20experiment%20with%20AI%20to%20take%20on%20more%20impactful%20work%20and%20perhaps%20shift%20what%20they're%20able%20to%20focus%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHumans%20are%20very%20good%20at%20adapting%20to%20their%20circumstances%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flower-cost-ai-deepseek-good-for-workers-productivity-boost-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738488182000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d3b6b7bb3f854015b6577%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flower-cost-ai-deepseek-good-for-workers-productivity-boost-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Low-cost%20AI%20could%20let%20more%20workers%20access%20the%20technology.%20That%20could%20boost%20productivity%20even%20as%20concerns%20