0electronics%20and%20electrical%20machinery%20to%20textiles%20and%20clothing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20yawning%20trade%20imbalance%20--%20%24270.4%20billion%20for%20January%20to%20November%20last%20year%20--%20has%20long%20raised%20hackles%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20has%20China's%20vast%20state%20support%20for%20its%20industries%2C%20sparking%20accusations%20of%20dumping%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20perceived%20mistreatment%20of%20US%20firms%20operating%20in%20its%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20China's%20economy%20remains%20heavily%20reliant%20on%20exports%20to%20drive%20growth%20despite%20official%20efforts%20to%20raise%20domestic%20consumption%20--%20making%20its%20leaders%20reluctant%20to%20change%20the%20status%20quo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happened%20during%20Trump's%20first%20term%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20stormed%20into%20the%20White%20House%20in%202016%20vowing%20to%20get%20even%20with%20China%2C%20launching%20a%20trade%20war%20that%20slapped%20significant%20tariffs%20on%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20Chinese%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20responded%20with%20retaliatory%20tariffs%20on%20US%20products%20--%20particularly%20affecting%20American%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20US%20demands%20were%20greater%20access%20to%20China's%20markets%2C%20broad%20reform%20of%20a%20business%20playing%20field%20that%20heavily%20favours%20Chinese%20firms%2C%20and%20a%20loosening%20of%20heavy%20state%20control%20by%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20long%2C%20fraught%20negotiations%20the%20two%20sides%20agreed%20what%20became%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bphase%20one%26quot%3B%20trade%20deal%20--%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20the%20nearly%20two-year-old%20trade%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20that%20agreement%2C%20Beijing%20agreed%20to%20import%20%24200%20billion%20worth%20of%20US%20goods%2C%20including%20%2432%20billion%20in%20farm%20products%20and%20seafood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20and%20a%20US%20recession%2C%20analysts%20say%20Beijing%20fell%20well%20short%20of%20that%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20end%2C%20China%20bought%20only%2058%20percent%20of%20the%20US%20exports%20it%20had%20committed%20to%20purchase%20under%20the%20agreement%2C%20not%20even%20enough%20to%20reach%20its%20import%20levels%20from%20before%20the%20trade%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20PIIE'S%20Chad%20P%20Brown%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPut%20differently%2C%20China%20bought%20none%20of%20the%20additional%20%24200%20billion%20of%20exports%20Trump's%20deal%20had%20promised.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20things%20change%20under%20Biden%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20successor%20Joe%20Biden%20did%20not%20roll%20back%20increases%20imposed%20by%20his%20predecessor%2C%20but%20took%20a%20more%20targeted%20approach%20when%20it%20came%20to%20tariff%20hikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Biden%2C%20Washington%20expanded%20efforts%20to%20curb%20exports%20of%20state-of-the-art%20chips%20to%20China%20--%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20effort%20to%20prevent%20sensitive%20US%20technologies%20being%20used%20in%20Beijing's%20military%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20administration%20also%20used%20tariffs%20to%20take%20aim%20at%20what%20it%20called%20China's%20%26quot%3Bindustrial%20overcapacity%26quot%3B%20--%20fears%20the%20country's%20industrial%20subsidies%20for%20green%20energy%2C%20cars%20and%20batteries%20could%20flood%20global%20markets%20with%20cheap%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20May%2C%20Biden%20ordered%20tariffs%20on%20%2418%20billion%20worth%20of%20imports%20from%20China%2C%20accusing%20Beijing%20of%20%26quot%3Bcheating%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20competing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20hikes%2C%20tariffs%20on%20electric%20vehicles%20quadrupled%20to%20100%20percent%2C%20while%20the%20tariff%20for%20semiconductors%20surged%20from%2025%20percent%20to%2050%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20measures%20also%20targeted%20strategic%20sectors%20such%20as%20batteries%2C%20critical%20minerals%20and%20medical%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20sides%20have%20also%20launched%20investigations%20into%20the%20others'%20alleged%20unfair%20trade%20practices%20with%20probes%20into%20dumping%20and%20state%20subsidies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20announcement%20on%20Saturday%20showed%20his%20long-threatened%20tariff%20hikes%20were%20serious%20and%20not%20an%20opening%20gambit%20in%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mercurial%20magnate%20has%20also%20tied%20tariffs%20to%20the%20fate%20of%20Chinese-owned%20social%20media%20app%20TikTok%20--%20warning%20of%20retaliation%20if%20a%20deal%20cannot%20be%20struck%20to%20sell%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Beijing's%20strong%20riposte%20has%20left%20little%20doubt%20that%20it%20will%20push%20back%20against%20measures%20it%20has%20long%20viewed%20as%20unfair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20commerce%20ministry%20has%20vowed%20%26quot%3Bcorresponding%20countermeasures%20to%20resolutely%20safeguard%20our%20own%20rights%20and%20interests%26quot%3B%2C%20without%20saying%20what%20form%20they%20will%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20said%20it%20will%20take%20its%20case%20against%20Trump's%20tariffs%20to%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organization%2C%20though%20that%20is%20unlikely%20to%20bring%20change%20in%20the%20short%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20immediate%20is%20the%20threat%20by%20Beijing's%20foreign%20ministry%20that%20the%20duties%20%26quot%3Bwill%20inevitably%20affect%20and%20damage%20future%20bilateral%20cooperation%20on%20drug%20control%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20casts%20a%20new%20shadow%20over%20counternarcotics%20talks%20that%20resumed%20after%20Biden%20met%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20in%20San%20Francisco%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20US-China%